{
  "texts": [
    "An important use of the ensemble of 10 KO networks is for estimating model uncertainty for a particular stimulus sequence.",
    "A single KO network can only give one prediction for a stimulus sequence (Fig. 4d,e); one may erroneously conclude that the model is equally certain about all stimulus sequences.",
    "Instead, the 1-to-1 network may be more uncertain for different stimulus sequences, especially those that are rarely observed during natural courtship.",
    "Thus, before experimentally testing the 1-to-1 network's predictions, one may first check if the 1-to-1 network is confident in its prediction by assessing the extent to which different network runs agree on the same prediction.",
    "If there is large agreement (as seen here), the 1-to-1 network is confident in its predictions."
  ]
}